&gt; Hi,
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;d like to propose a fix for JUnit test class reloading.  The  
&gt; proposed fix
&gt; is a Java 2 custom ClassLoader that loads test classes from its own
&gt; classpath and always delegates to the system/parent ClassLoader first
&gt; without relying on anything like excluded.properties to filter system  
&gt; and
&gt; non-system classes.
&gt;
&gt; note: this is how Servlets, JSPs, EJBs, etc. are reloaded dynamically  
&gt; on
&gt; change by J2EE containers that support dynamic reloads -- the Servlet,
&gt; JSPs,
&gt; EJBs, etc. are not on the system classpath, so the system classloader  
&gt; can
&gt; always be delegated to and will not find the classes and this leave it  
&gt; to
&gt; the custom loader(s) to load them.  All defined in the Java 2  
&gt; ClassLoader
&gt; delegation contract.
&gt;
&gt; The proposed means of configuring the custom loader&#39;s classpath is to  
&gt; use a
&gt; Java system property named &quot;junit.test.path&quot;.  This can be set as a  
&gt; command
&gt; line argument, or could be read from a properties file.
&gt;
&gt; I have implemented this proposal in a small patch that can be  
&gt; downloaded
&gt; here:
&gt; http://users.rcn.com/scottstirling/junit-patch.jar.
&gt;
&gt; A regression test (XmlTest.java) and series of steps for reproducing  
&gt; the
&gt; original TestCaseClassLoader bug and running the test with the patch  
&gt; are
&gt; here:
&gt; http://users.rcn.com/scottstirling/2003/07/19.html#a61
